    "ItemDescriptionContent": "Kashan",
    "ItemDescriptionCategory": "",
    "IsWatched": false,
    "WatchedByEmail": "",
    "DescriptionRuleID": 16,
    "DescriptionAuto": true,
    "DescriptionLong": "The Kashan Rug is among the oldest and finest in today’s market.  Known\nfor their overall beauty, Kashan Rugs originated in the city of Kashan – one of\nIran’s earliest cities. Persian Antique Kashan Rugs represent a key role in Persian silk production.\n\nIt has been suggested that Kashan designs go back to the early 16th century during the Safavid period. It is well-known that within the Persian Empire, Kashan was thought to be one of the most important trading centers along the famous Silk Road.\n\nThe foundation of Kashan rugs is usually cotton – though the older pieces were\noften created from pure silk.  Some of these unique silk designs often became\none-of-a-kind.  Today, the body frame of these rugs is crafted with high-quality\nsheep’s wool that can also be incorporated with silk.\n\nThe Kashan rugs are given pastel tones to provide a neutral and subtle effect, \nwhile the patterns are fleshed out with predominant shades of red, blue, indigo \nand ivory.  Some of the rugs also use the effect of color shading through weaving\ntechniques that add another level of depth.  Their dense knotting allows for a\nvariety of patterns which included medallions and floral ornamentation.\n\nThe finished texture of a Kashan is usually tight yet soft to the touch – and the\nKashan rug continues to sell well.  Because of the traditional, high production \nstandards of the Kashan rug, it remains one of the finest Persian carpets \navailable today.\n",
    "DescriptionShort": ""
  },
