    "DescriptionRuleID": 17,
    "DescriptionAuto": true,
    "DescriptionLong": "Nain carpets are considered among the finest, high quality rugs of Iran.  \nDepending upon knotting density, there are specific categories of Nain rugs.\n\nNain Rugs are popular because of their soft, calming palette of ivory with complementary sky and navy blues. They are often made of Kork wool which\nis usually finer than the standard Persian wool.  Their quality and fine knotting \nmake Nain rugs very desirable to rug connoisseurs and collectors.  In fact,\nsome of these rugs are made entirely of silk and many display a central \nmedallion surrounded by floral patterns.\n",
    "DescriptionShort": ""
  },
