    "DescriptionRuleID": null,
    "DescriptionAuto": false,
    "DescriptionLong": "A vintage Armenian workshop rug featuring a dense, all-over \"Kuba\" lattice design. The Madder \nRed field is covered with a complex, interlocking network of stylized ivory geometric figures, \nderived from the \"Kufic\" and \"Ram's Horn\" motifs of antique Shirvan and Perepedil weavings. \nThe precision of the repeat pattern and the stark red-and-ivory contrast are characteristic of the \nspecialized production of the Hay Gorg factories. The main border features a \"Running Dog\" or \n\"Reciprocal Trefoil\" guard, framing the intricate field.",
