    "DescriptionRuleID": 18,
    "DescriptionAuto": true,
    "DescriptionLong": "Isfahan carpets offer a wide range of traditional designs and colors with knotted\nwool pile being applied to either a silk or cotton foundation. By far the most\npopular design features a circular central medallion against a sculpted field of\npalmettes and floral representations.  \n\nGeometric medallions, trees with animals, or a tableaux of human and animal\npictorials are typical designs.  Weavers generally use no less than fifteen colors\nwhen creating an Isfahan carpet.  A particular terra cotta red is unique to these\nrugs in border accents and fields.\n\nThe Isfahan is one of the finest and most beautiful carpets in Iran.\n",
    "DescriptionShort": ""
  },
