    "DescriptionRuleID": 14,
    "DescriptionAuto": true,
    "DescriptionLong": "These striking hand knotted Oriental rugs stem from Armenia, Azerbaijan and Georgia between the 18th and 19th centuries. They are typically bright colored with vegetable dyes and known for their geometric patterns and meaningful symbols of Kazak culture. These symbols vary from medallions, Memling Guls, latch hook, cloud-bands and human or animal figures.\n\nThese rugs can withstand the test of time due to the natural dyes of the Azeri Turks. The ruby-reds, sapphire blues and ivory-off whites can last for centuries and stand out beautifully in neutral toned rooms.\n",
    "DescriptionShort": ""
